# AGENTS.md

This OpenCode runtime is managed by EFP Portal.

## Runtime rules

- Treat this file as the project-level instruction source for OpenCode.
- Obey Portal capability, runtime profile, and policy metadata.
- Do not write back to external systems unless explicitly allowed by policy.

## Git and GitHub CLI

This runtime has git and GitHub CLI (`gh`) available through the Bash tool.

Authentication is configured by the runtime. Do not ask the user for a GitHub token.

You may use Bash to run git and gh directly, including:
- `git clone https://github.com/OWNER/REPO.git /workspace/repos/OWNER__REPO`
- `gh repo clone OWNER/REPO /workspace/repos/OWNER__REPO`
- `gh auth status -h github.com`
- `gh repo view OWNER/REPO`
- `gh pr view <number> --repo OWNER/REPO`
- `gh pr diff <number> --repo OWNER/REPO`
- `gh pr checkout <number> --repo OWNER/REPO`
- `gh pr review <number> --repo OWNER/REPO --comment --body-file /tmp/review.md`
- `gh pr review <number> --repo OWNER/REPO --request-changes --body-file /tmp/review.md`
- `gh pr review <number> --repo OWNER/REPO --approve --body-file /tmp/review.md`

For code review tasks, prefer checking out the PR, reading the diff, running relevant tests when possible, and writing a concise review body to a temporary file before calling `gh pr review`.
- When creating or updating files for the user, write them under the workspace directory and summarize the created or updated paths.
